@realmoney Investors in Stocks and Bonds Today Have Never Been So Uninformed Summary: * The financial markets' DNA and structure have changed * The price momentum and dampened volatility delivered by mechanistic ETFs, quant and passive strategies in stocks and bonds combined

with the liquidity provided by central bankers' (in suppressing bond yields) have created the largest population of unknowledgeable traders and investors in history * Many of these products, strategies and players know everything about price but nothing about value *And that

means there is a lot of underappreciated risk and lack of liquidity in both equities and fixed income if and when the price momentum turns.. @jimcramer @tomkeene @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @Sarge986 @riskreversal @lizclaman @beckyquick @andrewrsorkin @realdonaldtrump
